        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 15 at 5:11PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 511 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles east of Kellerville, or 14 miles northwest of Shamrock, moving
southeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kellerville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
